{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.27",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 27,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 27",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 27 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:1",
      "text": "Job also added, taking up his parable, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:2",
      "text": "As God liveth, who hath taken away my judgment, and the Almighty, who hath brought my soul to bitterness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:3",
      "text": "As long as breath remaineth in me, and the spirit of God in my nostrils,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:4",
      "text": "My lips shall not speak iniquity, neither shall my tongue contrive lying.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:5",
      "text": "God forbid that I should judge you to be just: till I die I will not depart from my innocence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:6",
      "text": "My justification, which I have begun to hold, I will not forsake: for my heart doth not reprehend me in all my life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:7",
      "text": "Let my enemy be as the ungodly, and my adversary as the wicked one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:8",
      "text": "For what is the hope of the hypocrite if through covetousness he take by violence, and God deliver not his soul?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:9",
      "text": "Will God hear his cry, when distress shall come upon him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:10",
      "text": "Or can he delight himself in the Almighty, and call upon God at all times?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:11",
      "text": "I will teach you by the hand of God, what the Almighty hath, and I will not conceal it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:12",
      "text": "Behold you all know it, and why do you speak vain things without cause?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:13",
      "text": "This is the portion of a wicked man with God, and the inheritance of the violent, which they shall receive of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:14",
      "text": "If his sons be multiplied, they shall be for the sword, and his grandsons shall not be filled with bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:15",
      "text": "They that shall remain of him, shall be buried in death, and his widows shall not weep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:16",
      "text": "If he shall heap together silver as earth, and prepare raiment as clay,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:17",
      "text": "He shall prepare indeed, but the just man shall be clothed with it: and the innocent shall divide the silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:18",
      "text": "He hath built his house as a moth, and as a keeper he hath made a booth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:19",
      "text": "The rich man when he shall sleep shall take away nothing with him: he shall open his eyes and find nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:20",
      "text": "Poverty like water shall take hold on him, a tempest shall oppress him in the night:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:21",
      "text": "A burning wind shall take him up, and carry him away, and as a whirlwind shall snatch him from his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:22",
      "text": "And he shall cast upon him, and shall not spare: out of his hand he would willingly flee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.27.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:23",
      "text": "He shall clasp his hands upon him, and shall hiss at him, beholding his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
